	<body style="background-color: #000000">
		<header style="background-color: #59ea3a; color: #3ca0d0">
			<h1>Almond Green Salad</h1>
			
			<em><h2>Fresh and Crispy</h2></em>
		</header>
		
		<article style="background-color: #3ca0d0; color: #20805e">
			<h3>Ingredients</h3>
			
			1/2 pound bacon<br>
			2 tbls white wine vinegar<br>
			3 tbls honey<br>
			1/2 tsp mustard<br>
			1/2 tsp celery salt<br>
			1/2 tsp paprika<br>
			1/4 c olive oil<br>
			1 heaf red leaf lettuce-bite-sized<br>
			1 can mandarin oranges, drained,<br>
			1 bunch freen onions, diced<br>
			3/4 c slivered almond
		</article>
		
		
		<article style="background-color: #20805e">
			<h3>Directions</h3>
			
			<p>1. In medium skillet over medium-heat, cook bacon until evenly browned. Drain, cool, and crumble.</p>
			
			<p>2. Mix vinegar, honey, dry mustard, celery salt, paprika, and olive oil.</p>
			
			<p>3. Place lettuce, oranges, green onions, bacon, and almonds in serving bowl. Toss with dressing and serve.</p>
			
		</article>
	</body>
</html>